msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 33"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:0.5"
msgid "33. Paramparabhojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on eating a meal before another"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.76, pts-cs-bu-pc33.1, pts-vp-en.2.315, ms2V_716
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ paṇītānaṃ bhattānaṃ bhattapaṭipāṭi adhiṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr "At that time in Vesālī people had arranged a succession of fine meals."

#. VAR: kammakārassa → kammakarassa (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho aññatarassa daliddassa kammakārassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "And a certain poor worker thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.4"
msgid "“na kho idaṃ orakaṃ bhavissati yathayime manussā sakkaccaṃ bhattaṃ karonti; yannūnāhampi bhattaṃ kareyyan”ti."
msgstr "“Why don’t I prepare a meal? It won’t be inferior to the meal respectfully prepared by these people.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro yena kirapatiko tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He then went to his boss Kira"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ kirapatikaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.7"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, ayyaputta, buddhappamukhassa bhikkhusaṃghassa bhattaṃ kātuṃ."
msgstr "“Sir, I wish to prepare a meal for the Order of monks headed by the Buddha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.8"
msgid "Dehi me vetanan”ti."
msgstr "Please give me my salary.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.9"
msgid "Sopi kho kirapatiko saddho hoti pasanno."
msgstr "Because Kira also had faith and confidence,"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: abbhātirekaṃ → atirekaṃ (s1-3) | abbhatirekaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho so kirapatiko tassa daliddassa kammakārassa abbhātirekaṃ vetanaṃ adāsi."
msgstr "he gave the worker his salary and much extra."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards that worker went to the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.12"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.13"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so daliddo kammakāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.14"
msgid "“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, please accept a meal from me tomorrow together with the Order of monks.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.15"
msgid "“Mahā kho, āvuso, bhikkhusaṃgho, jānāhī”ti."
msgstr "“Do you know that the Order is large?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Hotu → hotu me (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.16"
msgid "“Hotu, bhante, mahā bhikkhusaṃgho."
msgstr "“Let the Order be large, Venerable Sir."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.316
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.17"
msgid "Bahū me badarā paṭiyattā badaramissena peyyā paripūrissantī”ti."
msgstr "I’ve prepared much jujube and also drinks mixed with jujube.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.18"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Master consented by remaining silent, and the worker understood."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.19"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "He rose from his seat, circumambulated the Master with his right side towards him, and left."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: ms2V_717
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.20"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū—"
msgstr "The monks heard that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.21"
msgid "“daliddena kira kammakārena svātanāya buddhappamukho bhikkhusaṃgho nimantito, badaramissena peyyā paripūrissantī”ti."
msgstr "a poor worker had invited the Order of monks headed by the Buddha for a meal on the following day, complete with drinks mixed with jujube."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.22"
msgid "Te kālasseva piṇḍāya caritvā bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "And so they ate in the morning after walking for alms."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.23"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho manussā—"
msgstr "When people heard that"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.24"
msgid "“daliddena kira kammakārena buddhappamukho bhikkhusaṃgho nimantito”ti."
msgstr "a poor worker had invited the Order of monks headed by the Buddha for a meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.25"
msgid "Te daliddassa kammakārassa pahūtaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ abhihariṃsu."
msgstr "they brought much food of various kinds to him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.26"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro tassā rattiyā accayena paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi—"
msgstr "The following morning that worker prepared that food, and then had the Master informed"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.27"
msgid "“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“It’s time, Venerable Sir, the meal is ready.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_718
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.28"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena tassa daliddassa kammakārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The Master robed up, took his bowl and robe, and together with the Order of monks, he went to the house of that poor worker,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.29"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena."
msgstr "where he sat down on the prepared seat in the dining hall."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.30"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro bhattagge bhikkhū parivisati."
msgstr "The worker served the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.31"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "but they kept saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.32"
msgid "“thokaṃ, āvuso, dehi. Thokaṃ, āvuso, dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Give just a little.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.33"
msgid "“Mā kho tumhe, bhante, ‘ayaṃ daliddo kammakāro’ti thokaṃ thokaṃ paṭiggaṇhittha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t accept so little because you think I’m just poor worker."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.34"
msgid "Pahūtaṃ me khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattaṃ."
msgstr "I’ve prepared much food of various kinds."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.35"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhatha, bhante, yāvadatthan”ti."
msgstr "Venerables, please accept as much as you like.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.36"
msgid "“Na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, etaṃkāraṇā thokaṃ thokaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr "“We’re not accepting so little because of that,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.37"
msgid "Api ca, mayaṃ kālasseva piṇḍāya caritvā bhuñjimhā; tena mayaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ paṭiggaṇhāmā”ti."
msgstr "but because we ate in the morning after walking for alms.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, pts-vp-en.2.317, ms2V_719
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.38"
msgid "Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That poor worker complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.39"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhadantā mayā nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Venerables eat elsewhere when invited by me?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.40"
msgid "Na cāhaṃ paṭibalo yāvadatthaṃ dātun”ti?"
msgstr "Am I not able to give as much as they need?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.77, ms2V_720
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.41"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa daliddassa kammakārassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that worker,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.42"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.43"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.44"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can those monks eat elsewhere when invited for a meal?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.45"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that monks did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.46"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.47"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.48"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissanti."
msgstr "How can those foolish men eat elsewhere when invited for a meal?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.49"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.50"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.50a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_721
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.51"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats a meal before another, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_722
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:1.52"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-pc33.2, pts-vp-en.2.318, ms2V_723
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a cetain monk became sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.2"
msgid "Aññataro bhikkhu piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Another monk took some almsfood, went to that monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.3"
msgid "“bhuñjāhi, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "and told him to eat it."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.4"
msgid "“Alaṃ, āvuso, atthi me bhattapaccāsā”ti."
msgstr "“I can’t; I’m expecting another meal.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: ussūre → ussūrena (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.5"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhuno piṇḍapāto ussūre āharīyittha."
msgstr "But that almsfood only arrived after midday,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.6"
msgid "So bhikkhu na cittarūpaṃ bhuñji."
msgstr "and that monk did not eat as much as he had intended."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.9"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat a meal before another."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.10"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.10a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_724
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.11"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats a meal before another, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.12"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.13"
msgid "Gilānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_725
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:2.14"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. VAR: paṭiyādetvā → paṭiyādāpetvā (si, pts1)
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc33.3, ms2V_726,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvaradānasamaye sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyādetvā bhikkhū nimantenti—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards, during the robe-giving season, people prepared a meal together with robe-cloth and then invited the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.2"
msgid "“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We wish to offer you a meal and give you robe-cloth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā paramparabhojanan”ti."
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating a meal before another and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.4"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "As a result they only obtained a small amount of robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.6"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another during the robe-giving season."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.7"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.7a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_727
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.8"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats a meal before another, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.9"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.10"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_728
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.11"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.11a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_729
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.12"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvarakārake bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards people invited monks who were making a robe for a meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.13"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā paramparabhojanan”ti."
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had prohibited eating a meal before another and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.14"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.15"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another when you are making a robe."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.16"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_730
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.17"
msgid "“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats a meal before another, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.18"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.19"
msgid "Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "he is sick, it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_731
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:3.20"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fifth sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc17, pts-vp-pli4.78, pts-cs-bu-pc33.4, ms2V_732
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āyasmatā ānandena pacchāsamaṇena yena aññataraṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards, the Master robed up in the morning, took his bowl and  robe, and went to a certain family with Venerable Ānanda as his attendant."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.319
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "He sat down on the prepared seat,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā bhagavato ca āyasmato ca ānandassa bhojanaṃ adaṃsu."
msgstr "and the people there gave staple food."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.4"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggaṇhāti."
msgstr "Being afraid of wrongdoing, Ānanda did not accept it."

#. VAR: Gaṇhāhi → patigaṇhāhi (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.5"
msgid "“Gaṇhāhi, ānandā”ti."
msgstr "The Master said, “Accept it, Ānanda.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.6"
msgid "“Alaṃ, bhagavā, atthi me bhattapaccāsā”ti."
msgstr "“I can’t, Master, I’m expecting another meal.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.7"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, vikappetvā gaṇhāhī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, transfer that meal to someone else and then receive this.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—“"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule">
#. VAR: bhikkhave, vikappetvā → bhattapaccāsaṃ vikappetvā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.9"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vikappetvā paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another if you transfer the other meal to someone else."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.10"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, vikappetabbaṃ—"
msgstr "And, monks, this is how it should be transferred:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:4.11"
msgid "‘mayhaṃ bhattapaccāsaṃ itthannāmassa dammī’”ti."
msgstr "‘I give my expected meal to so-and-so.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, pts-cs-bu-pc33.5.1, ms2V_733
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.1"
msgid "Paramparabhojanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Eats a meal before another:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.2"
msgid "pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantito, taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjati, etaṃ paramparabhojanaṃ nāma."
msgstr "if he has been invited to eat any of the five staple foods, and he then eats any of the five staple foods elsewhere—this is called “eats a meal before another.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms2V_734
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.3"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.4"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_735
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.5"
msgid "Gilānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is sick:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.6"
msgid "na sakkoti ekāsane nisinno yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjituṃ."
msgstr "if he is not able to eat as much as he needs in one session,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.7"
msgid "“Gilānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat a meal before another."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc21, ms2V_736
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is the robe-giving season:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
# NOTE: That is, the last month of the rainy season, plus the four months of the cold season.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.9"
msgid "anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañca māsā. “Cīvaradānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if he has not done the robe-making ceremony, he may eat a meal before another during the last month of the rainy season. If he has done the robe-making ceremony, he may eat a meal before another during the five month period."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc22, ms2V_737
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.10"
msgid "Cīvarakārasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is making a robe:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.11"
msgid "cīvare kayiramāne."
msgstr "if he is making a robe,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.12"
msgid "“Cīvarakārasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may eat a meal before another."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc23, ms2V_738
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.13"
msgid "“Aññatra samayā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives food with the intention of eating it, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.1.14"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc24, pts-cs-bu-pc33.5.2, ms2V_739
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.2.1"
msgid "Paramparabhojane paramparabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a meal before another, and he perceives it as a meal before another, and he eats it, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.2.2"
msgid "Paramparabhojane vematiko, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a meal before another, but he is unsure if it is, and he eats it, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.2.3"
msgid "Paramparabhojane naparamparabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a meal before another, but he does not perceive it as a meal before another, and he eats it, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25, ms2V_740
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.2.4"
msgid "Naparamparabhojane paramparabhojanasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a meal before another, but he perceives it as a meal before another, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.2.5"
msgid "Naparamparabhojane vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a meal before another, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.2.6"
msgid "Naparamparabhojane naparamparabhojanasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not a meal before another, and he does not perceive it as a meal before another, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc26, pts-cs-bu-pc33.5.3, ms2V_741
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.3"
msgid "vikappetvā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he transfers his other meal to someone else and then eats;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.320
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.4"
msgid "dve tayo nimantane ekato bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats the food from two or three invitations together;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.5"
msgid "nimantanapaṭipāṭiyā bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he eats the meals in the same order that the invitations were received;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.6"
msgid "sakalena gāmena nimantito tasmiṃ gāme yattha katthaci bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he is invited by a whole village and he eats anywhere in that village;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.7"
msgid "sakalena pūgena nimantito tasmiṃ pūge yattha katthaci bhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he is invited by a whole association and he eats anywhere within that association;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.8"
msgid "nimantiyamāno bhikkhaṃ gahessāmīti bhaṇati,"
msgstr "if, when being invited, he says, “I’ll get almsfood;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.9"
msgid "niccabhatte,"
msgstr "if it is a regular meal invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.10"
msgid "salākabhatte,"
msgstr "if it is a meal invitation decided by drawing lots;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.11"
msgid "pakkhike,"
msgstr "if it is a half-monthly meal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.12"
msgid "uposathike,"
msgstr "if it is on the observance day;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.13"
msgid "pāṭipadike,"
msgstr "if it is on the day after the observance day;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.14"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,"
msgstr "if it is anything apart from the five staple foods;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.15"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.16"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc27, ms2V_742
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc33:5.3.17"
msgid "Paramparabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The third rule, the training rule on eating a meal before another, is finished."
